5|$|W. S. Gilbert wrote a short comic play titled Rosencrantz and Guildenstern, in Hamlet's play is {{presented}} as a tragedy written by Claudius in his youth of which he is greatly embarrassed. Through the chaos triggered by Hamlet's staging of it, Guildenstern helps Rosencrantz vie with Hamlet to make Ophelia <b>his</b> <b>bride.</b>|$|E
